Two leaves precede part 1, containing in Greek: (f. 1r) Grammatical notes: excerpt from John VI Kantakouzenos, Orationes quatuor contra Mahometem, 1.3 and owner inscription: "Christiani Ravii Berlinatis". - (f. 1v) Table of contents. - (f. 2r) Epitaphium in Demetrium Cydonem / Manuel Calecas. - (f. 2r-v) Oraculum de restitutione Constantinopolis / Leo VI. - (f. 2v) Capita practica / Niketas Stethatos. - (f. 2v) Capita ascetica (CPG 7869) / Isaac of Nineveh (Isaac Syrus).; Part 1 contains excerpts from ascetic works and other texts, in Greek: (ff. 3r-19r) Sermones ascetici. - (ff. 19r-26r) Asceticon / Isaiah of Gaza (Isaia Abbas). - (ff. 26v-34v) Doctrinae diversae I-XVII / Dorotheus of Gaza. - (ff. 35r-49r) Canones apostolorum. With explanations ascribed to Macarius Chrysocephalus. - (ff. 49r-58r) Concilii Nicaeni (I) canones. Preceded by prologue (49r-v). - (f. 58r-v) Concilii Constantinopolitani (II) canones. Incomplete (only can. 1-2, due to missing leaves). Preceded by a prologue, with explanations by Theodore Balsamon and Joannes Zonaras (58r). - (ff. 59r-67r) Dicta patrum contra blasphemiam Latinorum. Includes: Symbolum synodi Constantinopolitanea (III, 60v-61r), adnotatio ad symbolum (61r), De septem synodis (61v-62r), commentarius in symbolum (62r-66v), De divinis nominibus (CPG 6602) / Pseudo-Dionysius the Areopagite. Excerpt (66v-67r). - Empty: ff. 67v-68v.; Part 2 contains excerpts from various church fathers, in Greek: (ff. 69r-70v) In Joannem homiliae 1-88 / John Chrysostom. - (ff. 70r-71v) In Acta Apostolorum homiliae 1-55 / John Chrysostom. - (ff. 71v-75v*) Dialogi de Sancta Trinitate / Maximus the Confessor. - (ff. 75v) Capita XV / Maximus the Confessor. - (ff. 75v-76v) Orationis Dominicae expositio / Maximus the Confessor. - (ff. 76v-78v) Expositio fidei / John of Damascus. - (ff. 78v) Pseudo-Clementina 6: Epitome de gestis Petri praemetaphrastica, dicta "altera". - (ff. 78v-79r) Pandectes / Nikon of the Black Mountain. - (ff. 79r-83r) Theologica 5 : De Spiritu Sancto (or. 31) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (f. 83r-v) In Matth. 19, 1-12 (or. 37) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (ff. 83v) Apologetica vel De fuga (or. 2) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (f. 85r-v) De moderatione in disputando (or. 32) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (ff. 85r-v,100-101v) Ep. 26 ad Evagrium monachum / Gregory of Nyssa. - (ff. 85v-87r) In Heronem (or. 25) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (f. 87r) De dogmate (or. 20) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (f. 87r-v) In sancta Lumina (or. 39) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (ff. 87v-88r) In sanctum baptisma (or. 40) / Gregory of Nazianzus. - (ff. 88r-89v) De vita S. Incomplete (due to lost leaves after f. 228).; Part 8 contains, in Greek: (ff. 229r-254v) De syntaxi / John XIII of Constantinople (John Glycis).; Part 9 contains, in Greek: (ff. 255r-273v) Lexicon: "Τεχνολογία γραμματικῆς". Incomplete. With inserted leaf (265r-v) Vitae sophistarum / Flavius Philostratus. Excerpt. - (ff. 274r-315r) Epimerismi / Georgius Lacapenus. Incomplete (lacks beginning). - (ff. 315r-316r) Opera / Michael Psellos (codex: Hypatos). - (ff. 316r-357r) De constructione verborum / Michael Synkellos. - (ff. 357v-359v) De passionibus dictionum / Tryphon of Alexandria. - (ff. 359v-361r) "Τεχνολογία γραμματικῆς". - (f. 361r-v) Scholia on Plato's Euthydemus, added in a later hand.; Part 10 contains, in Greek: (ff. 362r-366v) In thermas Pythicas / Paul the Silentiary. With scholia (365r-366v). - (ff. 366v-388v) Epigrams (36) from the Anthologia Palatina (selected from books 9-11). With interlinear glosses and marginal scholia. - (ff. 389v-392v) "Τεχνολογία γραμματικῆς". - (ff. 392v-393v) Lexicon / Maximus Planudes. Excerpts. - (ff. 394r-430v) Epiperismi / Maximus Planudes.; Part 11 contains, in Greek: (f. 431r-v) Vitae philosophorum / Laërtius Diogenes. Excerpt (from Vita Platonis). - (ff. 431v-460r) Excerpts from works by Plato: De justo, Axiochus, Definitiones, a.o. - (f. 460r) De specialibus legibus / Philo of Alexandria (Philo Judaeus). Excerpts. - (ff. 460v-461r) Homilia de legislatore / Severian of Gabala. Excerpts. - (f. 461r-v) Poemata / Michael Psellos. Fragment.; Two leaves follow part 11, containing in Greek: (ff. 462r-463r) Theologica / Michael Psellos. Excerpt. - (f. 463v) Pen trials.
